com.pb.sawdust.tabledata

Class FrozenTableKey<K>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pb.sawdust.tabledata.AbstractTableKey<K>
      • com.pb.sawdust.tabledata.FrozenTableKey<K>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - The type of the table key.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    TableIndex<K>, TableKey<K>

    public class FrozenTableKey<K>
extends AbstractTableKey<K>

    The FrozenTableKey is an immutable TableKey. Once instantiated, the key cannot be rebuilt, and should only be used for table data objects which are themselves immutable.

        Constructor which builds a frozen table key from a specified data table and one of its columns. This will create a table key "frozen" at the current state of the data table.
        Parameters:
        table - The data table upon which the key is to be built.
        columnLabel - The data table's column which this key will refer to.
        Throws:
        TableDataException - if the column does not exist in the data table, or if the column does not contain unique entries.

    • Method Detail

      • getKeyIndex

        protected InjectiveMap<K,java.lang.Integer> getKeyIndex()
        Description copied from class: AbstractTableKey
        Build a lookup table used to map key values to table data rows. This key index should be constructed such that getRowNumber(key) is identical to getKeyIndex().get(key). This method should account for changes made to the underlying/referring data table. That is, if a data table is altered in some manner, then subsequent calls to this method will reflect these changes. This mapping should be unique, so that no map value (row number) is repeated (matched to more than one key). The map's value set should form a complete set of all row numbers in the underlying/referring data table.
        Specified by:
        getKeyIndex in class AbstractTableKey<K>
        Returns:
        the mapping from key values to row numbers.
